    second wife, Mary Welford (1781–1848), daughter of a 
    retired merchant of Blackheath. He was nearly sixty-four, 
    she was twenty-eight years old. By 1812 they had separated. Godwin visits them 
    (technically, he visits the poet, an increasing recluse, on a trip in August 1811. 
  He did not take to Hayley, but is fulsome in his praise for Hayley's wife in a letter to Mary Jane.
